57-8. Periurus leno, as Ballio in the Pseudolus. Meretrix mala, as Phronesium in the Truculentus. Miles gloriosus, as Pyrgopolinices in the Miles. The stock-characters of the New Comedy are enumerated by Terence 111 the prologue to the Eunuchus (vv. 35 sqq.):

Quod si personis isdem huic uti non licet,

Qui magis licet currentem seruom scribere, Bonas matronas facere, meretrices malas, Parasitum edacem, gloriosum militem,

Puerum supponi, falli per scruom senem,

Amare, odisse, suspicari? denique

Nullumst iam dictum quod non sit dictum prius,

and by Apuleius Florida 111. xvi. 64 Hild. : leno periurus et amator-feruidus et seruulus callidus et amica ‘illudens et umor inhibens et mater indulyens et patruus obiuryutor et pas-entes tenaces et meretrices procaces.
